We decided to hold a brunch party and booked it in advance. We even called 2 days before to confirm as what we were told to do they can have the proper staff.  We arrived and it took 30 mins to even have someone ask what we wanted. There seemed to be only one person manning the place and he wasn’t even the owner. I feel bad for him because he did try with effort, but it wasn’t his fault. The person seemed as if he was the host, waiter, and bartender for a party of 20. That was a set up for failure!!! I could only imagine if there were other customers at the time. The owner knew about the party 3 weeks in advance and we even called days before the event. It was poorly managed. It’s a shame because the place has potential. I was mad and embarrassed for my birthday. We all decided to get up and leave, because we saw where this was heading if we continued to stay...we didn’t want to waist our time and have whoever was working that day hustle and bustle because of poor management. About 1/2 hour in some of our party received their appetizers. As the rest of us waited, we saw paramedics come inside around 2 pm. We later learned it was one of the cooks who needed them. We asked the waitress should we stay or leave; was the food coming; etc. Some of our party cancelled and left. Finally around 2:25 the manager comes over to our table. We inform him that he should have come over and explained to us the situation, and maybe offered us a complimentary drink, or pastry, or something.  He was clueless, but he finally agreed to a few slices of cheese cake, carrot cake and cannolis. We were told our orders were coming in 5 minutes, but food did not arrive for about 20 minutes!
